Entitled “Resurrect”, the 5th episode of 180, the music series, witnesses the musical encounter between @che_lingo and @gaikasees. A plunge into the heart of London brought back to life through @davidktom’s camera. This collaborative piece mixes rap lyrics, different voice tonalities and electronic beats in a soul-grabbing track entitled “Resurrect” which calls for new energy and new beginnings.

#AudemarsPiguet #APxMusic

node.text:
Thank you to those who joined us live on April 10 to celebrate the official launch of our collaboration with Marvel, and the reveal of a limited-edition Royal Oak Concept Flying Tourbillon dedicated to Black Panther.
The live event, which was publicly broadcast around the world, was hosted by stand-up comedian and actor Kevin Hart alongside Audemars Piguet’s Chief Executive Officer François-Henry Bennahmias, with LeBron James, Serena Williams, Ian Poulter, Anthony Joshua, Lu Han, Jon Gray and Mark Ronson in attendance

A unique version of the Royal Oak Concept “Black Panther” Flying Tourbillon timepiece was auctioned off during the event to support the long-term educational programme Audemars Piguet has established with First Book and Ashoka.

#AudemarsPiguet #APxMarvel

Discover “Paradise”, the new episode of the music series 180.  An intriguing encounter of universes where beats and percussions, poetic lyrics and punchlines, English and Lingala, come together in harmony. 

@jeanneadded and music duo @tshegue_official  were given three days and a complete carte blanche to create and record an original soundtrack bringing their music universes together. 
An experience enhanced by the spontaneous freestyle of @officiallestwins , captured on a virtual stage by @originalkidsparis.

This miniseries retraces the unconventional challenge Audemars Piguet set to selected rising music artists. Their mission: go beyond their comfort zone and create an original collaborative soundtrack blending different creative universes.

#AudemarsPiguet #APxMusic

A dream came true for @thelyonz!
Experience THe LYONZ’s one-of-a-kind performance in a surrealistic landscape, organised in collaboration with the @montreuxjazzfestival.
Recorded in the mountains above Montreux, the complex scenography puts this live concert in the footstep of the creative challenges set to emerging music artists as part of the miniseries 180, in which the Canadian duo took part.
 
Watch the long version on our YouTube Channel.
#AudemarsPiguet #APxMusic #MJF21
